article.description: — Lenell Henry had a career-high 22 points as Alcorn State defeated Jackson State 65-50 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Henry scores 22 to carry Alcorn St. past Jackson St. 65-50
article.linkText: Henry scores 22 to carry Alcorn St. past Jackson St. 65-50
article.story: JACKSON, Miss. -- — Lenell Henry had a career-high 22 points as Alcorn State defeated Jackson State 65-50 on Wednesday night. Both teams were playing their first Southwestern Athletic Conference game of the season. Dominic Brewton had 14 points for Alcorn State (2-11, 1-0 Southwestern Athletic Conference), which snapped its six-game losing streak. Justin Thomas added seven rebounds. Jonas James III had 15 points for the Tigers (2-10, 0-1), who have now lost four games in a row. Gabe Watson added 14 points. Jayveous McKinnis had 14 points and four blocks. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
